MongoDB (Legacy) Documentation
Historically, MongoDB was used as the primary data storage solution for DiscountMate.
As the platform transitions to a PostgreSQL‑based ETL pipeline, the resources in this folder serve as legacy documentation for reference and archival purposes.

Contents
MongoDB SOP – T1 2026.pdf  
A SOP outlining how MongoDB has been used within DiscountMate, including database structure, workflows, and operational guidelines.

MongoDBUploadScript_Woolworths.ipynb  
Notebook used during T1 2026 to upload weekly Woolworths prices to MongoDB.

IGA_Preprocessing_Script_20260516
Notebook used during T1 2026 to upload weekly IGA prices to MongoDB.

Coles_Preprocessing_Script_20260516.ipynb
Notebook used during T1 2026 to upload weekly Coles prices to MongoDB.

Status
These files will be deprecated and are maintained here predominately for historical context.
Once the PostgreSQL migration is fully complete, this folder will no longer be required.
